<subSubSection id="DD9F6544FFD37B0AAB9134CBA68FFDD0" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="953A36CFFFD37B0AAB9134CBA68FFDD0" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,1797]" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">
<emphasis id="A7F1EADDFFD37B0AAB9134CBA34CFF5D" bold="true" box="[199,322,150,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species can be recognised by the light brown forewing with indistinct marking, darkened costal margin and fold weakly mottled with dark brown. A distinct medial expansion on the valva, broad sacculus, very short vincular processes, stout wide saccus and slender, long and apically bifurcated phallus are characteristic for the male genitalia. This suite of characters is unique and is not observed in any other 
<taxonomicName id="52854D4CFFD37B0AAF39355FA765FEF1" box="[1135,1387,258,284]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Scrobipalpula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="A7F1EADDFFD37B0AAF39355FA703FEF1" box="[1135,1293,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">Scrobipalpula</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
The female genitalia can immediately be recognised by a large egg-shaped bulge on right side near the entrance of ductus bursae and by the absence of signum. A somewhat similar corpus bursae with posterior expansions and reduced signum is characteristic for 
<taxonomicName id="52854D4CFFD37B0AAA873533A180FE65" authority="(Meyrick, 1917)" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1917" box="[465,910,366,392]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Scrobipalpula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="densata">
<emphasis id="A7F1EADDFFD37B0AAA873533A0C0FE65" box="[465,718,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">Scrobipalpula densata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="F1144B3EFFD37B0AA98B3533A188FE65" author="Meyrick" box="[733,902,366,392]" firstAuthor="Meyrick" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" pagination="1 - 52" refId="ref6751" refString="Meyrick, E. (1917) Descriptions of South American Micro-Lepidoptera. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, 1, 1 - 52. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1917. tb 01401. x" type="journal article" year="1917">Meyrick, 1917</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="52854D4CFFD37B0AA8903533A763FE65" authority="Povolny, 1990" authorityName="Povolny" authorityYear="1990" box="[966,1389,366,392]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Scrobipalpula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fjeldsai">
<emphasis id="A7F1EADDFFD37B0AA8903533A6B3FE65" box="[966,1213,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">Scrobipalpula fjeldsai</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F1144B3EFFD37B0AAF903533A763FE65" author="Povolny" box="[1222,1389,366,392]" firstAuthor="Povolny" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" pagination="153 - 223" refId="ref7163" refString="Povolny, D. (1990) Gnorimoschemini of Peru and Bolivia (Lepidoptera: Gelechiidae). Steenstrupia, 16, 153 - 223." type="journal article" year="1990">Povolný, 1990</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but the corpus bursae in these species bears two posterior expansions rather than one as in 
<taxonomicName id="52854D4CFFD37B0AAF2335CEA6D4FE41" authority="Bidzilya &amp; Chang, 2022" authorityName="Bidzilya &amp; Chang" authorityYear="2022" box="[1141,1242,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Scrobipalpula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="onorei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="A7F1EADDFFD37B0AAF2335CEA6D4FE41" box="[1141,1242,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">S. onorei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="BCC257A6FFD37B0AAFB535CEA733FE40" box="[1251,1341,403,429]" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and the antrum is considerably shorter (
<bibRefCitation id="F1144B3EFFD37B0AA95135EBA0D7FE3D" author="Povolny" box="[519,729,438,464]" firstAuthor="Povolny" page="96" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" pagination="51 - 127" refId="ref6890" refString="Povolny, D. (1967) Genitalia of some nearctic and neotropic members of the tribe Gnorimoschemini (Lepidoptera, Gelechiidae). Acta entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 37, 51 - 127." type="journal article" year="1967">Povolný 1967: 96</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 91 (as 
<taxonomicName id="52854D4CFFD37B0AA83D35EBA721FE3D" authority="(Meyrick, 1917)" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1917" box="[875,1327,438,464]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Magnifacia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aulorrhoa">
<emphasis id="A7F1EADDFFD37B0AA83D35EBA669FE3D" box="[875,1127,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">Magnifacia aulorrhoa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="F1144B3EFFD37B0AAF2F35EBA729FE3D" author="Meyrick" box="[1145,1319,438,464]" firstAuthor="Meyrick" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" pagination="1 - 52" refId="ref6751" refString="Meyrick, E. (1917) Descriptions of South American Micro-Lepidoptera. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, 1, 1 - 52. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1917. tb 01401. x" type="journal article" year="1917">Meyrick, 1917</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="F1144B3EFFD37B0AAE6935EBA304FE19" author="Povolny" firstAuthor="Povolny" page="190" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" pagination="153 - 223" refId="ref7163" refString="Povolny, D. (1990) Gnorimoschemini of Peru and Bolivia (Lepidoptera: Gelechiidae). Steenstrupia, 16, 153 - 223." type="journal article" year="1990">Povolný 1990: 190</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 49; 
<bibRefCitation id="F1144B3EFFD37B0AAA3A3587A0F7FE19" author="Landry &amp; Roque-Albelo" box="[364,761,474,500]" firstAuthor="Landry" page="762" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" pagination="697 - 770" refId="ref6527" refString="Landry, B. &amp; Roque-Albelo, L. (2010) The Gelechiidae (Lepidoptera) of the Galapagos Islands, Ecuador, a taxonomic revision. Revue suisse de Zoologie, 117 (4), 697 - 770. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 117601" type="journal article" year="2010">Landry &amp; Roque-Albelo 2010: 762</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 90; 
<bibRefCitation id="F1144B3EFFD37B0AA80C3587A617FE19" author="Cepeda" box="[858,1049,474,500]" firstAuthor="Cepeda" page="26" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" pagination="21 - 30" refId="ref5732" refString="Cepeda, D. (2019) Descriptions of two new species of the genus Scrobipalpomima Povolny (Lepidoptera: Gelechiidae) y dos nuevos registros de Gnorimoschemini para Chile. Revista Chilena de Entomologia, 45 (1), 21 - 30." type="journal article" year="2019">Cepeda 2019: 26</bibRefCitation>
, figs 21, 22). 
<taxonomicName id="52854D4CFFD37B0AAFE43587A33DFDF5" authority="(Zeller, 1877)" baseAuthorityName="Zeller" baseAuthorityYear="1877" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Scrobipalpula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ilyella">
<emphasis id="A7F1EADDFFD37B0AAFE43587A792FE19" box="[1202,1436,474,500]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">Scrobipalpula ilyella</emphasis>
(Zeller, 1877)
</taxonomicName>
has also a somewhat similar bipartite corpus bursae, but differs in a less sclerotized and posteriorly constricted antrum (
<bibRefCitation id="F1144B3EFFD37B0AAA21367FA016FDD1" author="Povolny" box="[375,536,546,572]" firstAuthor="Povolny" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" pagination="51 - 127" refId="ref6890" refString="Povolny, D. (1967) Genitalia of some nearctic and neotropic members of the tribe Gnorimoschemini (Lepidoptera, Gelechiidae). Acta entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 37, 51 - 127." type="journal article" year="1967">Povolný 1967</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 126; 
<bibRefCitation id="F1144B3EFFD37B0AA9DF367FA129FDD1" author="Povolny" box="[649,807,546,572]" firstAuthor="Povolny" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" pagination="205 - 213" refId="ref7000" refString="Povolny, D. (1981) A redescription of Scrobipalpula ilyella (Zeller, 1877) b. n. in Peru and its importance as a pest of tobacco (Lepidoptera, Gelechiidae). Acta Universitatis Agriculturae, 29 (3 - 4), 205 - 213." type="journal article" year="1981">Povolný 1981</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 3; 
<bibRefCitation id="F1144B3EFFD37B0AA82B367FA613FDD1" author="Povolny" box="[893,1053,546,572]" firstAuthor="Povolny" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" pagination="153 - 223" refId="ref7163" refString="Povolny, D. (1990) Gnorimoschemini of Peru and Bolivia (Lepidoptera: Gelechiidae). Steenstrupia, 16, 153 - 223." type="journal article" year="1990">Povolný 1990</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 55).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DD9F6544FFD37B0AAB91361BA6FEF9BD" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" type="description">
<paragraph id="953A36CFFFD37B0AAB91361BA740FC6C" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,1797]" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">
<emphasis id="A7F1EADDFFD37B0AAB91361BA3ACFD8D" bold="true" box="[199,418,582,608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">Description. Adult</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="0DBE2A4AFFD37B0AAAE4361BA019FD8C" box="[434,535,582,609]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,1134,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-272@1.[155,1432,1134,1863]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Scrobipalpula onorei sp. nov., adult. 1. Male, holotype. 2. Head, lateral view, male, holotype. 3. Head, frontolateral view, female, paratype. 4, 5. Head, thorax and basal part of wings, ventral view. Arrow indicates hair pencil. 4. Male, holotype. 5. Female, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571588" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571588/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">Figs 1–5</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 
<quantity id="527D9B2AFFD37B0AA9F2361BA12EFD8C" box="[676,800,582,609]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" unit="mm" value="14.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="13.0">13–15 mm</quantity>
. Head, thorax and tegulae light brown, frons lighter, offwhite, labial palpus strongly upcurved and far protruded over head, palpomere 2 white on upper and inner side, outer surface distinctly mixed with light brown, underside with brush of modified scales, dark brown with greyish-white tips, palpomere 3 about half length and half width of palpomere 2, white with broad brown basal and medial belt (
<figureCitation id="0DBE2A4AFFD37B0AABC9368BA308FD1D" box="[159,262,726,752]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,1134,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-272@1.[155,1432,1134,1863]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Scrobipalpula onorei sp. nov., adult. 1. Male, holotype. 2. Head, lateral view, male, holotype. 3. Head, frontolateral view, female, paratype. 4, 5. Head, thorax and basal part of wings, ventral view. Arrow indicates hair pencil. 4. Male, holotype. 5. Female, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571588" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571588/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">Figs 2, 3</figureCitation>
); scape light brown with grey apex, flagellomeres brown grey-ringed; base of forewing underside with pencil of long black hairs in male and brown hairs in female (
<figureCitation id="0DBE2A4AFFD37B0AA80636A7A1B8FCF8" box="[848,950,762,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,1134,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-272@1.[155,1432,1134,1863]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Scrobipalpula onorei sp. nov., adult. 1. Male, holotype. 2. Head, lateral view, male, holotype. 3. Head, frontolateral view, female, paratype. 4, 5. Head, thorax and basal part of wings, ventral view. Arrow indicates hair pencil. 4. Male, holotype. 5. Female, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571588" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571588/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">Figs 4, 5</figureCitation>
); forewing (
<figureCitation id="0DBE2A4AFFD37B0AAF1436A7A68DFCF9" box="[1090,1155,762,788]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,1134,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-272@1.[155,1432,1134,1863]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Scrobipalpula onorei sp. nov., adult. 1. Male, holotype. 2. Head, lateral view, male, holotype. 3. Head, frontolateral view, female, paratype. 4, 5. Head, thorax and basal part of wings, ventral view. Arrow indicates hair pencil. 4. Male, holotype. 5. Female, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571588" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571588/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) covered with light grey brown- to ochreous-brown tipped scales, costal margin mottled with dark brown to 2/3¬3/4 length, ochreous suffusion along veins, two diffuse brown spots in cell, fold slightly mottled with dark brown, very indistinct diffuse white transverse subapical fascia at 3/4, cilia grey brown-tipped; hindwing grey with darker veins, cilia light grey.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="953A36CFFFD37B0AAB9137D7A62BFADD" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,1797]" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">
<emphasis id="A7F1EADDFFD37B0AAB9137D7A37FFC49" bold="true" box="[199,369,906,932]" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="0DBE2A4AFFD37B0AAA2837D7A3EEFC48" box="[382,480,906,933]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1914,1938]" captionTargetBox="[151,1424,184,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-21@2.[151,1435,181,1890]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 6–8. Scrobipalpula onorei sp. nov. 6, 7, Male genitalia. 6. Holotype male, unrolled, gen. slide 206/21, O. Bidzilya. 7. Ventral view, paratype male, gen. slide 218/21, O. Bidzilya, 8. Female genitalia, paratype, gen. slide 212/21, O. Bidzilya." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571590/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">Figs 6, 7</figureCitation>
). Uncus subrectanguar, slightly longer than broad, weakly constricted medially, posterior margin gradually bent, with short medial incision; transtilla pillow-like, extending to 3/4 length of uncus; gnathos twice shorter than uncus, gradually narrowed from base to mid length, then widened, distal margin with pointed adducted lateral corners and very short medial hump; tegumen broad at base, then narrowed to 2/3 and widened before uncus, anteromedial emargination broadly rounded, extending to half length of tegumen; valva weakly curved from base to 1/3, then direct, with distinct expansion at 1/3, covered with hairs in distal 2/3, apex rounded, extending to posterior margin of uncus; sacculus about 2/3 width and 1/7–1/8 length of valva, weakly curved inwards, with pointed tip; vinculum as broad as long, anteromedial emargination narrow, V-shaped, vincular processes as right triangular, with distinct tip, shorter than sacculus; saccus stout, broad, narrowed apically, far extending beyond top of pedunculus; phallus as long as combined length of saccus and tegumen, slender, weakly broadened from base to 1/3, then gradually narrowed towards rounded apex, straight, weakly bent at 1/3, dorsal side with short subapical process, bulbus ejaculatorius rounded or moderately elongated, lamina indistinct.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="953A36CFFFD37B0AAB913167A6FEF9BD" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,1797]" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">
<emphasis id="A7F1EADDFFD37B0AAB913167A385FAB9" bold="true" box="[199,395,1338,1364]" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="0DBE2A4AFFD37B0AAACF3167A3D2FAB9" box="[409,476,1338,1364]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1914,1938]" captionTargetBox="[151,1424,184,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-21@2.[151,1435,181,1890]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 6–8. Scrobipalpula onorei sp. nov. 6, 7, Male genitalia. 6. Holotype male, unrolled, gen. slide 206/21, O. Bidzilya. 7. Ventral view, paratype male, gen. slide 218/21, O. Bidzilya, 8. Female genitalia, paratype, gen. slide 212/21, O. Bidzilya." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571590/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Papillae anales short, subtriangular, covered with strong setae; apophyses posteriores about 3.5x as long as segment VIII and about 2.5x as long as apophyses anteriores; segment VIII subrectangular, about as broader as long; subgenital plates about 1/3 width of sternum VIII, with fold at distal 1/4 of medial margin and slender sclerotised band extending from base of apophyses anteriores to 3/4 of medial margin; apophyses anteriores longer than sternite VIII, weakly bent at 2/3; ductus bursae very slender, broadened in distal 1/5, colliculum long, strongly sclerotised, antrum funnel-shaped, strongly sclerotised laterally, anteriorely narrowing and extending to 2/3 length of apophyses anteriores; corpus bursae as long as ductus bursae with antrum, gradually broadened anteriorly, with large egg-shaped bulge on right side near the entrance of ductus bursae; no signum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
