<subSubSection id="DD9F6544FFD37B0AAB91329BA3B5F8E9" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="953A36CFFFD37B0AAB91329BA3B5F8E9" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,1797]" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">
<emphasis id="A7F1EADDFFD37B0AAB91329BA340F90D" bold="true" box="[199,334,1734,1760]" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is named in honour of Prof. Giovanni Onore (Quito, 
<collectingCountry id="ED92765FFFD37B0AAF0E329BA6B4F90C" box="[1112,1210,1734,1761]" name="Ecuador" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
), the collector of the 
<typeStatus id="4A3E886DFFD37B0AABC132B6A2C9F8E8" box="[151,199,1771,1797]" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">type</typeStatus>
series of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
